WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.442 --> 00:00:10.312
Brought you a Bible. Lonnie.

2
00:00:10.313 --> 00:00:13.081
Little late for saving souls.
ain't it. preacher?

3
00:00:13.082 --> 00:00:15.380
I'd suggest Luke 21:36.

4
00:00:15.383 --> 00:00:18.423
"Pray always. that ye may
be accounted worthy"

5
00:00:18.424 --> 00:00:21.089
"to escape
all these things."

6
00:00:52.318 --> 00:00:53.048
What do you think's in there?

7
00:00:53.054 --> 00:00:56.664
What say you open it up. stick
your head in and take a gander?

8
00:01:08.468 --> 00:01:10.898
Charliehorse.
we're under attack...

9
00:01:34.961 --> 00:01:38.601
You've murdered my friends
and colleagues.

10
00:01:38.731 --> 00:01:43.436
You blackmailed a man I
hold in the highest esteem.

11
00:01:43.437 --> 00:01:46.906
You seem to have a comprehensive
knowledge of my life

12
00:01:46.907 --> 00:01:50.477
that you could only realize
through an association

13
00:01:50.478 --> 00:01:52.678
with someone close to me.

14
00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:54.249
You don't recognize me. do you?

15
00:01:54.250 --> 00:01:55.878
I want to know who hired you.

16
00:01:55.883 --> 00:01:57.783
Gavin Pruitt was my husband.

17
00:01:57.785 --> 00:02:02.645
Most people think the danger in a
situation like this is the cold.

18
00:02:02.656 --> 00:02:07.086
The more immediate danger
is the oxygen supply.

19
00:02:08.094 --> 00:02:08.894
Answer my question.

20
00:02:08.896 --> 00:02:13.396
or you will suffocate long
before you freeze to death.

21
00:02:14.134 --> 00:02:16.541
Gavin set up your
tax havens in Mauritius.

22
00:02:16.542 --> 00:02:19.706
When the feds got to him.
you thought he would talk.

23
00:02:19.707 --> 00:02:21.037
So you had him killed.

24
00:02:21.041 --> 00:02:22.741
I want a name.

25
00:02:25.712 --> 00:02:27.952
Raymond. it's Cooper.

26
00:02:30.316 --> 00:02:33.446
Harold. what can I do for you?

27
00:02:33.887 --> 00:02:35.517
Give me back my prisoner.

28
00:02:35.523 --> 00:02:36.023
Which prisoner?

29
00:02:36.024 --> 00:02:38.493
You know exactly who I'm
talking about. Reddington.

30
00:02:38.494 --> 00:02:39.892
Isabella stone.

31
00:02:40.360 --> 00:02:40.890
She's perfectly safe.

32
00:02:40.895 --> 00:02:43.655
I have every intention of
returning her to your custody

33
00:02:43.664 --> 00:02:46.366
as soon as she's given me
the information I need.

34
00:02:46.367 --> 00:02:46.897
<i>You've gone too far.</i>

35
00:02:46.901 --> 00:02:50.270
I just came from main justice.
They threatened to shut us down.

36
00:02:50.271 --> 00:02:51.801
They're bluffing.
<i>Are they?</i>

37
00:02:51.805 --> 00:02:52.466
From their point of view.

38
00:02:52.473 --> 00:02:54.673
you've become a bigger
liability than an asset.

39
00:02:54.675 --> 00:02:57.135
Harold. what's happening here?
You sound desperate.

40
00:02:57.144 --> 00:03:00.647
From the beginning. this has been
all about serving your agenda.

41
00:03:00.648 --> 00:03:01.447
And I've rolled
with that because

42
00:03:01.448 --> 00:03:05.018
I genuinely believe this task force
makes the world a safer place.

43
00:03:05.019 --> 00:03:06.988
You aren't being naive.
<i>You're damn right!</i>

44
00:03:06.989 --> 00:03:10.187
Not anymore. Now. I want a name.
I want a big one.

45
00:03:10.191 --> 00:03:12.260
Not some independent
contractor like stone.

46
00:03:12.261 --> 00:03:14.659
You can't just order up
super-criminals

47
00:03:14.662 --> 00:03:16.829
like Chinese takeout. Harold.

48
00:03:16.830 --> 00:03:18.330
I want it now.

49
00:03:20.133 --> 00:03:21.868
The architect.

50
00:03:21.869 --> 00:03:22.899
London. 2014.

51
00:03:22.903 --> 00:03:25.803
A tanker loading
diesel fuel explodes.

52
00:03:25.939 --> 00:03:26.669
Ten minutes later.

53
00:03:26.674 --> 00:03:29.512
a water main fails.
flooding Covent garden.

54
00:03:29.513 --> 00:03:32.080
Only after authorities pumped
out the water did they realize

55
00:03:32.081 --> 00:03:35.809
$100 million in diamonds had
been stolen from a nearby vault.

56
00:03:35.816 --> 00:03:38.946
<i>According to Reddington. this
was the work of the architect.</i>

57
00:03:38.953 --> 00:03:41.693
<i>who for a price
will design. construct</i>

58
00:03:41.694 --> 00:03:44.159
<i>and execute the perfect crime.</i>

59
00:03:44.457 --> 00:03:45.257
Cortina. Italy. 2011.

60
00:03:45.259 --> 00:03:48.928
A safety canon malfunctions. setting
off a devastating avalanche.

61
00:03:48.929 --> 00:03:52.459
Two weeks earlier. a Brazilian art
collector's home was broken into.

62
00:03:52.466 --> 00:03:54.996
<i>Nothing of value was stolen.
but panicked by the break-in.</i>

63
00:03:55.002 --> 00:03:59.402
<i>the collector shipped a Caravaggio
to a secure facility in Geneva</i>

64
00:03:59.406 --> 00:04:01.636
<i>whose director would be
killed in the avalanche.</i>

65
00:04:01.642 --> 00:04:04.911
<i>The man who signed for the
old master was an imposter</i>

66
00:04:04.912 --> 00:04:06.012
<i>and the Caravaggio disappeared.</i>

67
00:04:06.013 --> 00:04:10.120
<i>Reddington says the architect is
in Philadelphia recruiting hackers</i>

68
00:04:10.121 --> 00:04:12.986
at an underground gathering
called black mass 13.

69
00:04:12.987 --> 00:04:14.487
Sounds like a slasher movie.

70
00:04:14.488 --> 00:04:16.458
More like a ghost story.

71
00:04:16.856 --> 00:04:18.986
Black mass is where
the worst of the worst compete

72
00:04:18.993 --> 00:04:21.293
to see who can hack
a set of security measures.

73
00:04:21.295 --> 00:04:24.325
The winner's supposed to be
hired for the type of gig

74
00:04:24.331 --> 00:04:26.301
that you don't come back from
with a soul.

75
00:04:26.302 --> 00:04:29.769
CP. industrial sabotage.
real horror-show stuff.

76
00:04:29.770 --> 00:04:33.670
Multiple hits on a hexadecimal
embedded in postings

77
00:04:33.674 --> 00:04:38.744
containing the words
"black". "mass". and "13".

78
00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:40.475
And we have...

79
00:04:40.481 --> 00:04:43.249
We have a GPS coordinate
in Philadelphia.

80
00:04:43.250 --> 00:04:44.380
The location of the convention?

81
00:04:44.385 --> 00:04:48.445
Nope. This is just the first
step down the rabbit hole.

82
00:04:49.722 --> 00:04:54.162
<i>All right. guys. look for
anything out of the ordinary.</i>

83
00:05:00.166 --> 00:05:01.566
Hey. keen.

84
00:05:10.376 --> 00:05:14.506
"If foo equals
first object oriented."

85
00:05:14.515 --> 00:05:16.175
"Enter". then "bar".

86
00:05:16.183 --> 00:05:21.921
then an "equals" sign. then the
words "binary arbitrary reason".

87
00:05:21.922 --> 00:05:24.022
Totally what I was gonna say.

88
00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:29.760
1955 south Hartford. Havertown.

89
00:05:29.763 --> 00:05:30.803
What are we gonna do
when we get there?

90
00:05:30.804 --> 00:05:35.428
It's all about pattern recognition.
Just keep your eyes open.

91
00:05:42.408 --> 00:05:44.438
Hey. Did you talk
to Richard game?

92
00:05:44.445 --> 00:05:46.305
No. but I think I was wrong.

93
00:05:46.313 --> 00:05:48.448
About what? Game confessed
to killing you.

94
00:05:48.449 --> 00:05:50.249
He's dead. Turns out
his mother's still alive.

95
00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:53.750
So I'm going to see her.
Maybe she has some answers.

96
00:05:53.754 --> 00:05:54.854
But wait. what were
you wrong about?

97
00:05:54.855 --> 00:05:57.585
<i>I didn't really care what
Richard game had to tell me</i>

98
00:05:57.591 --> 00:05:58.891
until I found out he was dead.

99
00:05:58.892 --> 00:06:00.230
and now it's all I want to know.

100
00:06:00.231 --> 00:06:01.757
Who my father was.
Who I was.

101
00:06:01.762 --> 00:06:04.132
Why somebody wanted the world
to believe I was dead.

102
00:06:04.133 --> 00:06:06.931
<i>That's what I was wrong about.
saying it didn't matter to me.</i>

103
00:06:06.934 --> 00:06:09.168
But you were right.
It does.

104
00:06:09.169 --> 00:06:12.099
<i>I'll call you
if I found anything out.</i>

105
00:06:16.442 --> 00:06:18.080
We're here.
See anything weird?

106
00:06:18.081 --> 00:06:20.878
I'm not loving the idea
of a rabbit-food smoothie.

107
00:06:20.881 --> 00:06:22.811
but other than that. no.

108
00:06:22.816 --> 00:06:24.446
Can you send me a photo?

109
00:06:31.758 --> 00:06:33.388
Okay. I got it!

110
00:06:33.760 --> 00:06:36.900
I'll have a penny candy. please.

111
00:06:41.901 --> 00:06:42.901
Thank you.

112
00:06:42.903 --> 00:06:45.473
Oh. my god. There are
so many combinations.

113
00:06:45.474 --> 00:06:47.072
This is gonna take hours.

114
00:06:47.074 --> 00:06:48.944
Here. let me see that.

115
00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:56.750
How long did that take?

116
00:07:03.356 --> 00:07:05.016
Agent Ressler. a word?

117
00:07:05.025 --> 00:07:06.425
I'll give this to Aram.

118
00:07:06.427 --> 00:07:06.887
Found an SD chip.

119
00:07:06.894 --> 00:07:10.564
Aram should be able to use it
to locate the black mass.

120
00:07:11.664 --> 00:07:15.634
Reven Wright was my superior
and my friend.

121
00:07:15.636 --> 00:07:17.166
So I don't like this
any more than you.

122
00:07:17.171 --> 00:07:19.271
but the inquiry
into her disappearance...

123
00:07:19.273 --> 00:07:20.273
Reven Wright didn't disappear.

124
00:07:20.274 --> 00:07:23.009
She was murdered by Laurel Hitchin.
We know that.

125
00:07:23.010 --> 00:07:23.910
The inquiry is being shut down.

126
00:07:23.911 --> 00:07:28.648
The president's national
security advisor is a murderer.

127
00:07:28.649 --> 00:07:29.849
There's no evidence of that.

128
00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:31.820
No witnesses.
No prints. No case.

129
00:07:31.821 --> 00:07:34.519
The head of the justice division
doesn't just disappear.

130
00:07:34.521 --> 00:07:37.721
But until we can prove it.
the case is closed.

131
00:07:37.724 --> 00:07:41.394
Okay. I got something. It's
a pick-up point. I think.

132
00:07:41.395 --> 00:07:43.695
248 Garfield. 3:20 P.M.

133
00:07:43.697 --> 00:07:45.797
It says. "come alone
and wear a yellow hat."

134
00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:47.569
We need to get an agent
to that pick-up point

135
00:07:47.570 --> 00:07:49.968
to get into black mass
to ID the architect.

136
00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:50.938
Yeah. but whoever we send in

137
00:07:50.939 --> 00:07:52.438
would have to really
know their stuff.

138
00:07:52.439 --> 00:07:56.039
Not just the programing but
the buzzwords. the culture.

139
00:07:56.043 --> 00:07:57.413
It's gonna...

140
00:08:01.080 --> 00:08:03.080
No. I can't.
Not after last time.

141
00:08:03.083 --> 00:08:04.821
- You were amazing last time.
- Which part?

142
00:08:04.822 --> 00:08:06.488
Getting beaten to a pulp
by my psycho girlfriend

143
00:08:06.489 --> 00:08:10.187
or screaming our safe word like a
baby who needs his diaper changed?

144
00:08:10.190 --> 00:08:12.120
The architect
is a mass murderer.

145
00:08:12.125 --> 00:08:14.655
This is our only chance
to catch him.

146
00:08:14.861 --> 00:08:16.731
We need you to do this.

147
00:08:35.849 --> 00:08:37.179
We're hot.

148
00:08:49.162 --> 00:08:54.272
I believe that will
do the job quite nicely.

149
00:08:58.804 --> 00:09:01.207
Are you getting the CCTV feeds?

150
00:09:01.208 --> 00:09:02.668
Okay. we have eyes.

151
00:09:02.676 --> 00:09:04.476
Yellow hat. Gray blazer.

152
00:09:04.478 --> 00:09:05.478
Very handsome.

153
00:09:05.479 --> 00:09:07.279
And the TAC team is standing by.

154
00:09:07.281 --> 00:09:08.711
They'll be in place
as soon as you give us

155
00:09:08.715 --> 00:09:09.709
a location for
the black mass site.

156
00:09:09.716 --> 00:09:13.286
So when I ID the architect.
they're gonna breach. right?

157
00:09:14.620 --> 00:09:16.150
All right. Here we go.

158
00:09:30.503 --> 00:09:31.873
Put this on.

159
00:09:33.339 --> 00:09:35.809
Now. Let's go.

160
00:09:38.044 --> 00:09:41.284
We're right here with you.
We're not going anywhere.

161
00:09:41.285 --> 00:09:44.216
There's a man I know
who works as a docent

162
00:09:44.217 --> 00:09:46.947
in a small museum
in the northwest.

163
00:09:46.954 --> 00:09:48.554
He recently remarried.

164
00:09:48.555 --> 00:09:52.115
Rotary Tuesdays.
Euchre Fridays.

165
00:09:52.425 --> 00:09:54.755
A modest. but happy life.

166
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:57.031
Gavin and I played euchre.

167
00:09:58.564 --> 00:10:00.374
Before you killed him.

168
00:10:00.766 --> 00:10:03.536
Gavin was a brilliant accountant

169
00:10:04.337 --> 00:10:06.667
and an even better man

170
00:10:07.540 --> 00:10:09.170
who worshipped you.

171
00:10:09.176 --> 00:10:11.676
When the feds
came asking questions

172
00:10:11.678 --> 00:10:15.408
about the nature
of his relationship with me.

173
00:10:15.415 --> 00:10:16.375
his only thoughts

174
00:10:16.383 --> 00:10:19.483
were about whether
you and your children

175
00:10:19.486 --> 00:10:22.586
would be safe
and well-provided for.

176
00:10:22.589 --> 00:10:26.419
This person you described...
I didn't kill your husband.

177
00:10:26.426 --> 00:10:30.556
I helped him walk away
from everything he loved

178
00:10:30.564 --> 00:10:32.604
to protect you

179
00:10:32.798 --> 00:10:35.028
and your innocence.

180
00:10:35.735 --> 00:10:37.035
Ironic.

181
00:10:38.237 --> 00:10:40.037
Where is he?

182
00:10:40.773 --> 00:10:42.608
Who hired you?

183
00:10:42.609 --> 00:10:45.009
I got an anonymous package.

184
00:10:45.511 --> 00:10:48.247
detailing files

185
00:10:48.248 --> 00:10:51.748
about every aspect
of your operations.

186
00:10:51.752 --> 00:10:52.252
And your payment?

187
00:10:52.253 --> 00:10:55.152
I received a credit stick.
It's in my apartment.

188
00:10:55.155 --> 00:10:59.185
It's in the lining
of a red silk dress.

189
00:11:00.159 --> 00:11:02.559
Now. my husband.

190
00:11:03.729 --> 00:11:05.429
Where is he?

191
00:11:06.499 --> 00:11:08.329
He's married.

192
00:11:08.501 --> 00:11:10.501
He remembers you as you were.

193
00:11:10.504 --> 00:11:15.174
To show him what you've become
would be devastating.

194
00:11:15.307 --> 00:11:18.077
I'm not going to tell you
where he is.

195
00:11:18.911 --> 00:11:20.711
But I will turn the heat up.

196
00:11:20.714 --> 00:11:23.784
You must be chilled to the bone.

197
00:11:24.383 --> 00:11:26.652
Aram. we're tracking you
through Lexington park.

198
00:11:26.653 --> 00:11:29.723
You're going northeast
on Algon Avenue.

199
00:11:30.089 --> 00:11:31.589
What's going on?

200
00:11:32.158 --> 00:11:33.218
Bring up another camera.

201
00:11:33.226 --> 00:11:35.726
Must be some sort of
jamming software.

202
00:11:35.729 --> 00:11:36.729
Aram.

203
00:11:36.730 --> 00:11:38.698
<i>Aram.</i>

204
00:11:38.699 --> 00:11:39.498
<i>Aram.</i>

205
00:11:39.499 --> 00:11:41.829
Cough twice if you can hear me.

206
00:11:46.405 --> 00:11:47.167
Contact tactical aviation.

207
00:11:47.174 --> 00:11:49.644
Give them specs on the Van
and a radius to work with.

208
00:11:49.645 --> 00:11:52.613
I want surveillance images
within 10 minutes.

209
00:12:02.354 --> 00:12:03.724
Who are you?

210
00:12:04.423 --> 00:12:06.323
Uh. Ms. Lucy game?

211
00:12:06.326 --> 00:12:07.156
My name is Frank Carraro.

212
00:12:07.160 --> 00:12:10.129
If I could just have a moment of
your time. it's about your son.

213
00:12:10.130 --> 00:12:13.030
My son is dead.
Have some respect.

214
00:12:13.033 --> 00:12:13.933
I'm with the innocence project.

215
00:12:13.934 --> 00:12:15.904
And we believe that your son
spent time in prison

216
00:12:15.905 --> 00:12:18.172
for a crime he did not commit.

217
00:12:19.472 --> 00:12:22.772
His name was
Christopher Hargrave.

218
00:12:23.676 --> 00:12:24.436
Yeah. I remember.

219
00:12:24.444 --> 00:12:26.644
Before he confessed.
did he talk to anyone?

220
00:12:26.646 --> 00:12:29.976
A lawyer or his cell mate?
Did anyone approach him?

221
00:12:29.983 --> 00:12:33.183
You obviously
didn't know my boy.

222
00:12:33.186 --> 00:12:36.016
Richard killed a lot of people.

223
00:12:36.022 --> 00:12:38.822
Took them apart
in the garage out back.

224
00:12:38.825 --> 00:12:43.155
He did things to them
I'll never forget.

225
00:12:43.763 --> 00:12:45.433
Finding out what really
happened. at this point.

226
00:12:45.434 --> 00:12:48.302
would make a huge difference
to the people

227
00:12:48.303 --> 00:12:50.031
who cared about
Christopher Hargrave.

228
00:12:50.036 --> 00:12:52.336
Your services had better be used

229
00:12:52.339 --> 00:12:55.769
for someone who
didn't belong in prison.

230
00:12:56.475 --> 00:13:00.405
Richard never belonged
anywhere else.

231
00:13:03.182 --> 00:13:05.052
Wait right here.

232
00:13:05.251 --> 00:13:06.651
All right. move.

233
00:13:08.421 --> 00:13:10.261
Wait right here.

234
00:13:34.180 --> 00:13:36.180
You looking for work?

235
00:13:36.183 --> 00:13:38.951
You know. if the job's right.

236
00:13:38.952 --> 00:13:42.092
What do you know about
batch credit card spoofing?

237
00:13:42.093 --> 00:13:46.088
I've done some.
for cartels mostly.

238
00:13:47.359 --> 00:13:50.029
Not that you look like
you work for a cartel.

239
00:13:50.030 --> 00:13:52.330
Maybe you do.
How would I know?

240
00:13:52.332 --> 00:13:56.102
I'm... excuse me.
I think I see an old friend.

241
00:13:59.171 --> 00:14:03.241
Excuse me. Aren't you
supposed to be in jail?

242
00:14:06.413 --> 00:14:07.313
Now's not a good time.

243
00:14:07.314 --> 00:14:10.716
Oh. really? I'm sorry.
Am I inconveniencing you?

244
00:14:10.717 --> 00:14:12.447
I said not now.

245
00:14:13.987 --> 00:14:17.256
<i>Yeah!
Five minutes to hackstar!</i>

246
00:14:17.257 --> 00:14:20.287
<i>Nut up and get your hack on!</i>

247
00:14:21.862 --> 00:14:27.066
<i>Whoa! Not a piggy-backed sql
injection like a rank amateur.</i>

248
00:14:27.067 --> 00:14:30.027
<i>Getting tense. getting tense.</i>

249
00:14:30.036 --> 00:14:30.697
<i>Come on. wizards.</i>

250
00:14:30.704 --> 00:14:32.144
<i>Second prize
is a set of steak knives.</i>

251
