502
00:28:05.084 --> 00:28:07.484
<i>one of the most secure
prisons in America.</i>

503
00:28:07.486 --> 00:28:08.616
<i>home to Virginia's death row.</i>

504
00:28:08.621 --> 00:28:11.521
<i>which is why they sent
Lonnie Perkins there.</i>

505
00:28:11.524 --> 00:28:12.123
<i>The cop killer.</i>

506
00:28:12.124 --> 00:28:14.562
<i>And President of the
Aryan revolutionary council.</i>

507
00:28:14.563 --> 00:28:17.060
Right now. they're the biggest
white supremacist gang

508
00:28:17.063 --> 00:28:17.962
in the prison system.

509
00:28:17.963 --> 00:28:20.098
Perkins is scheduled
to be executed tonight.

510
00:28:20.099 --> 00:28:21.899
You think this is all about
breaking out Perkins?

511
00:28:21.901 --> 00:28:23.831
The arc is exactly
the kind of organization

512
00:28:23.836 --> 00:28:25.896
that would have the resources
to hire the architect.

513
00:28:25.905 --> 00:28:28.665
Even if he took control of the
prison's internal systems.

514
00:28:28.674 --> 00:28:31.843
they're not just going to
let Perkins walk out.

515
00:28:31.844 --> 00:28:33.044
What's the Ace up his sleeve?

516
00:28:33.045 --> 00:28:35.705
On my signal. you will execute
a remote takeover

517
00:28:35.715 --> 00:28:39.345
of the software controlling the
internal operations of the prison.

518
00:28:39.351 --> 00:28:41.051
Do you have any idea
how many firewalls

519
00:28:41.053 --> 00:28:43.323
are built into
a system like that?

520
00:28:43.521 --> 00:28:43.991
Twenty-six.

521
00:28:43.992 --> 00:28:47.689
All disabled. thanks to a
state-wide blackout we created.

522
00:28:47.693 --> 00:28:50.093
Even if that's true.
the prison's operating system

523
00:28:50.096 --> 00:28:51.696
is physically segregated
from the Internet.

524
00:28:51.697 --> 00:28:54.997
Only way anyone could communicate
with the software...

525
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:59.900
Is if someone inside the
prison installed a back door.

526
00:29:11.917 --> 00:29:13.017
I'd like the door open. please.

527
00:29:13.018 --> 00:29:17.318
In case any of our visitors feel
the need to step out for air.

528
00:29:18.389 --> 00:29:19.519
It's locked.
I didn't close it.

529
00:29:19.525 --> 00:29:23.655
<i>Warden Mccaslin.
honored guests of the state.</i>

530
00:29:23.662 --> 00:29:28.102
please direct your attention
to guard tower 5.

531
00:29:35.306 --> 00:29:36.936
Three.

532
00:29:36.942 --> 00:29:38.309
two.

533
00:29:38.310 --> 00:29:39.780
one.

534
00:29:51.055 --> 00:29:54.255
It's gone.
The tower. it's gone.

535
00:30:08.840 --> 00:30:10.440
The breakout. it's started.

536
00:30:10.442 --> 00:30:11.042
What did Cooper say?

537
00:30:11.043 --> 00:30:14.283
A guard tower in Greenville
has just been destroyed.

538
00:30:14.579 --> 00:30:15.809
Any news about Aram?

539
00:30:21.920 --> 00:30:24.189
That was your
second guard tower. warden.

540
00:30:24.190 --> 00:30:29.660
For the sake of those in the third.
I do hope I have your attention.

541
00:30:38.503 --> 00:30:41.513
Oh. god. I love
the smell of oil paints.

542
00:30:42.040 --> 00:30:43.170
Ah...

543
00:30:43.175 --> 00:30:44.305
Almost more than gasoline.

544
00:30:44.310 --> 00:30:50.180
Why are there certain toxic smells
that just grab you that way?

545
00:30:52.618 --> 00:30:55.748
<i>Come Si dice. er...</i>
"Kidnapping"?

546
00:30:57.189 --> 00:31:00.059
You speak Italian?
There was a girl.

547
00:31:00.358 --> 00:31:01.328
Of course there was.

548
00:31:01.329 --> 00:31:04.487
Tell polpetto that I'm
a great admirer of his work.

549
00:31:04.496 --> 00:31:08.566
Not so much his nudes. They're
a hair splayed for my taste.

550
00:31:08.567 --> 00:31:13.167
And that I do apologize.
but I require his services.

551
00:31:16.175 --> 00:31:18.435
<i>What you're witnessing. warden.</i>

552
00:31:18.444 --> 00:31:20.144
<i>are solid titanium rods</i>

553
00:31:20.145 --> 00:31:22.405
<i>traveling at mach 7.</i>
Who are you?

554
00:31:22.414 --> 00:31:23.354
It's not important who I am.

555
00:31:23.355 --> 00:31:26.419
What's important is that I
have control of your prison.

556
00:31:26.420 --> 00:31:28.418
Once you release Lonnie Perkins.

557
00:31:28.420 --> 00:31:30.989
I will return
that control to you.

558
00:31:30.990 --> 00:31:32.190
That isn't going to happen.

559
00:31:32.191 --> 00:31:33.521
<i>The next rod
will strike the room</i>

560
00:31:33.525 --> 00:31:35.325
<i>where you and your guests
are standing.</i>

561
00:31:35.327 --> 00:31:39.197
You have 30 seconds. warden.
to release Perkins.

562
00:31:46.071 --> 00:31:48.309
The whole prison's locked down. sir.
All personnel.

563
00:31:48.310 --> 00:31:50.837
Sounds like you don't have
much of a choice. warden.

564
00:31:50.843 --> 00:31:53.113
I can still have that man
put a needle in your arm.

565
00:31:53.114 --> 00:31:56.382
If I go down.
you're going down with me.

566
00:31:57.882 --> 00:31:58.852
Target acquired.

567
00:31:58.853 --> 00:32:00.919
Prepare to fire on my mark.

568
00:32:00.920 --> 00:32:03.420
Please. you can't do this.

569
00:32:03.521 --> 00:32:04.521
Last chance. warden.

570
00:32:04.523 --> 00:32:08.633
<i>Mach 7 leaves very little
time for equivocation.</i>

571
00:32:14.632 --> 00:32:16.202
Let him go.

572
00:32:21.273 --> 00:32:21.643
It's Cooper.

573
00:32:21.644 --> 00:32:24.879
<i>Intersection of Mesa and
Ridgeline road. get there now.</i>

574
00:32:24.880 --> 00:32:26.737
You have a location
for the architect?

575
00:32:26.745 --> 00:32:27.075
And Aram.

576
00:32:27.079 --> 00:32:30.309
He's reached out using a device
he got from Janet Sutherland.

577
00:32:30.316 --> 00:32:31.176
That bitch?

578
00:32:31.183 --> 00:32:32.783
She's sitting right here.

579
00:32:32.785 --> 00:32:33.215
Hey. Samar.

580
00:32:33.218 --> 00:32:36.648
Turns out your boyfriend picked
up the remote code Cypher

581
00:32:36.655 --> 00:32:37.115
during the attack.

582
00:32:37.122 --> 00:32:39.592
<i>It's meant to transmit data.
which it's doing now.</i>

583
00:32:39.593 --> 00:32:42.860
The data is meaningless.
but the signal is traceable.

584
00:32:42.861 --> 00:32:44.061
He's sending an SOS.

585
00:32:44.063 --> 00:32:46.033
<i>At the end
of the hall is a door.</i>

586
00:32:46.034 --> 00:32:50.271
<i>Once you pass through.
turn left to 1A yard.</i>

587
00:32:50.535 --> 00:32:52.235
Cycle gate 13.

588
00:32:58.176 --> 00:33:00.906
<i>Turn left. proceed 20 feet.</i>

589
00:33:00.913 --> 00:33:04.048
<i>Two doors later
you'll see "inprocessing."</i>

590
00:33:04.049 --> 00:33:05.479
<i>Turn right.</i>

591
00:33:15.393 --> 00:33:16.193
Open the gate.

592
00:33:16.195 --> 00:33:19.325
If I set him free. more innocent
people are going to die.

593
00:33:19.331 --> 00:33:21.261
Just open the gate.

594
00:33:21.266 --> 00:33:22.966
Please. don't.

595
00:33:23.901 --> 00:33:24.301
What is that?

596
00:33:24.303 --> 00:33:27.541
Oh. that's... I don't...
No. no. please. please...

597
00:33:27.542 --> 00:33:29.069
What do you think you're doing?

598
00:33:29.074 --> 00:33:29.774
Nothing... I just...

599
00:33:29.775 --> 00:33:33.835
If you shoot me. you'll never
be able to open the gate.

600
00:33:33.846 --> 00:33:36.146
Just do it now.

601
00:33:36.148 --> 00:33:37.408
Yes.

602
00:33:58.703 --> 00:34:00.403
You can't do this.

603
00:34:00.406 --> 00:34:01.906
I already have.

604
00:34:25.063 --> 00:34:26.097
No. no. no.

605
00:34:26.098 --> 00:34:28.068
Watch him.
He's getting away!

606
00:34:29.100 --> 00:34:30.900
Don't let him get away!

607
00:34:32.970 --> 00:34:33.540
Alert local authorities.

608
00:34:33.541 --> 00:34:36.839
A black suburban is going up
Ridgeline Avenue. southwest.

609
00:34:36.842 --> 00:34:39.712
Look. if he leaves now.
we lose him for good.

610
00:34:40.044 --> 00:34:41.584
What are you doing?

611
00:34:41.879 --> 00:34:45.249
He escapes. more people die.

612
00:35:17.548 --> 00:35:18.618
Polpetto.

613
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:28.559
Reddington.

614
00:35:28.560 --> 00:35:31.090
Oh. my goodness.
this is tedious.

615
00:35:31.329 --> 00:35:33.459
I'd give almost anything
to have a scratch.

616
00:35:33.465 --> 00:35:35.725
But seeing as how.
given your profession. David.

617
00:35:35.734 --> 00:35:37.334
you might be more inclined
to squeeze them

618
00:35:37.336 --> 00:35:39.896
rather than scratch them.
I won't impose.

619
00:35:39.905 --> 00:35:42.235
I'll just wait
for the next break.

620
00:35:42.241 --> 00:35:42.940
What's he...

621
00:35:42.941 --> 00:35:44.141
Why is he painting
your portrait?

622
00:35:44.143 --> 00:35:46.543
I only brought him here
to leverage you to kill him

623
00:35:46.545 --> 00:35:49.805
unless you give me
the name of the depositor

624
00:35:49.815 --> 00:35:52.045
who has declared war.

625
00:35:52.050 --> 00:35:53.718
but once I properly
introduced myself.

626
00:35:53.719 --> 00:35:55.149
the little fella
just lit right up.

627
00:35:55.154 --> 00:35:59.024
I didn't fly him all the
way here to paint your...

628
00:36:00.191 --> 00:36:02.161
Where is my portrait?

629
00:36:02.293 --> 00:36:03.431
He needed the canvas.

630
00:36:03.432 --> 00:36:06.358
Turns out he's a huge fan
of spaghetti westerns.

631
00:36:06.365 --> 00:36:08.795
The anti-hero.
the outlaw. you know.

632
00:36:08.800 --> 00:36:10.400
That's quite enough.

633
00:36:10.402 --> 00:36:12.372
Out.
Shh!

634
00:36:23.881 --> 00:36:27.451
He is the sweetest man.

635
00:36:27.552 --> 00:36:30.121
It's going to break my heart
to put a bullet in his head.

636
00:36:30.122 --> 00:36:32.992
but that's what will happen
unless you tell me

637
00:36:32.993 --> 00:36:36.327
who at your bank
is coming after me.

638
00:36:36.328 --> 00:36:37.258
You wouldn't.
I would.

639
00:36:37.262 --> 00:36:40.462
In fact. what better way
to assure my place in history.

640
00:36:40.465 --> 00:36:43.995
The last portrait by
a master. unfinished.

641
00:36:44.002 --> 00:36:45.002
killed by his subject.

642
00:36:45.003 --> 00:36:47.543
And you without a portrait at all.
It's a shame.

643
00:36:47.544 --> 00:36:52.979
My business is based
on absolute privacy.

644
00:36:53.644 --> 00:36:56.214
Okay. okay. okay.
Just stop.

645
00:36:57.548 --> 00:37:00.748
Give me the stick
and I'll look into it.

646
00:37:00.752 --> 00:37:06.322
But you have to promise.
please. spare the man's life.

647
00:37:07.758 --> 00:37:10.728
We'll see how the portrait
turns out.

648
00:37:11.762 --> 00:37:13.602
For agent Ressler.

649
00:37:14.565 --> 00:37:15.825
Hey.

650
00:37:19.570 --> 00:37:22.039
Case files. Reven
Wright's disappearance.

651
00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:25.340
I thought Cooper said
that inquiry was closed.

652
00:37:25.344 --> 00:37:27.014
Not to me it isn't.

653
00:37:28.179 --> 00:37:29.979
I just got off
with the DC field office.

654
00:37:29.982 --> 00:37:32.852
Perkins and the driver
were stopped on I-274.

655
00:37:32.853 --> 00:37:34.521
They're in custody now.

656
00:37:34.785 --> 00:37:36.815
I told you you would be amazing.

657
00:37:36.822 --> 00:37:38.660
You don't have to say that.

658
00:37:38.661 --> 00:37:40.187
It's true.

659
00:37:44.895 --> 00:37:46.695
I killed a man today.

660
00:37:49.667 --> 00:37:53.367
And by killing him. I prevented
us from interrogating him.

661
00:37:53.372 --> 00:37:59.082
from getting information on his
other cases and clients. victims.

662
00:37:59.310 --> 00:38:01.750
Aram. you did the right thing.

663
00:38:05.449 --> 00:38:08.349
She's the reason
we were able to find you.

664
00:38:08.919 --> 00:38:10.549
Hey. uh. Janet.

665
00:38:15.059 --> 00:38:16.529
Uh...

666
00:38:16.761 --> 00:38:20.501
I'm probably only alive
because of you.

667
00:38:21.132 --> 00:38:23.032
so thank you for that.

668
00:38:23.467 --> 00:38:25.736
It doesn't make up for...

669
00:38:25.737 --> 00:38:27.337
You know.

670
00:38:29.907 --> 00:38:31.467
You should go.

671
00:38:37.081 --> 00:38:38.981
Hey. Aram.

672
00:38:41.986 --> 00:38:43.546
I am sorry.

673
00:38:57.468 --> 00:38:59.798
Don't.

674
00:39:02.173 --> 00:39:02.613
The mother?

675
00:39:02.614 --> 00:39:05.907
She was paid $100.000 to
convince her son to confess.

676
00:39:05.911 --> 00:39:08.351
She admitted it. that's great.

677
00:39:09.113 --> 00:39:10.381
Who paid her?

678
00:39:10.382 --> 00:39:12.082
She doesn't know.

679
00:39:12.084 --> 00:39:13.451
How is that possible?

680
00:39:13.452 --> 00:39:14.122
She was paid in cash.

681
00:39:14.123 --> 00:39:17.689
Half came in the script and half
came after game was convicted.

682
00:39:18.122 --> 00:39:19.090
A script?

683
00:39:19.091 --> 00:39:20.921
It has every detail.

684
00:39:21.025 --> 00:39:23.125
The color of the beach house.

685
00:39:23.128 --> 00:39:25.058
The tear in the screen door.

686
00:39:25.063 --> 00:39:27.463
The knife block where
the murder weapon was found.

687
00:39:27.466 --> 00:39:30.226
The pajamas you were wearing.
Yeah.

688
00:39:30.235 --> 00:39:32.535
The night light in the hall.

689
00:39:33.804 --> 00:39:35.242
Is any of this accurate?

690
00:39:35.243 --> 00:39:38.540
It has to be. right? I mean.
I don't remember any of it.

691
00:39:38.543 --> 00:39:40.283
You should show this
to your mother.

692
00:39:40.284 --> 00:39:42.378
She probably knows something.

693
00:39:42.381 --> 00:39:43.280
No.

694
00:39:43.281 --> 00:39:46.617
Her pain about losing
her son seems real.

695
00:39:46.618 --> 00:39:49.348
but Reddington says
I can't trust her.

696
00:39:49.354 --> 00:39:51.554
That if I tell her I'm her son.

697
00:39:51.556 --> 00:39:53.856
I'll never get the answers
I'm looking for.

698
00:39:53.859 --> 00:39:57.759
Based on this. it seems like the
only way you will is if you do.

699
00:39:57.763 --> 00:40:00.433
I just want to know
what was there to gain

700
00:40:00.434 --> 00:40:02.400
from me disappearing.

701
00:40:02.401 --> 00:40:03.631
And why was it so important

702
00:40:03.635 --> 00:40:05.995
that someone confessed
to my murder.

703
00:40:06.004 --> 00:40:10.444
And whoever wrote this.
what could they possibly want?

704
00:40:14.945 --> 00:40:16.175
Yeah.

705
00:40:20.785 --> 00:40:25.285
Harold. it troubles me
that you're dissatisfied

706
00:40:25.290 --> 00:40:27.560
with the results of our efforts.

707
00:40:28.225 --> 00:40:31.995
Doing good for selfish reasons
doesn't make you good.

708
00:40:32.096 --> 00:40:34.996
It just makes you good
at being selfish.

709
00:40:36.801 --> 00:40:38.971
I'm sorry about your daughter.

710
00:40:39.670 --> 00:40:44.240
You've never spoken of her around
me. which of course. I understand.

711
00:40:44.242 --> 00:40:48.142
But you've seemed
anxious of late.

712
00:40:48.679 --> 00:40:51.549
When someone you love is sick.

713
00:40:51.550 --> 00:40:55.490
you don't need to
shoulder that burden alone.

714
00:40:55.619 --> 00:40:57.919
My daughter isn't a burden.

715
00:40:58.155 --> 00:41:00.285
She's my greatest blessing.

716
00:41:01.725 --> 00:41:03.155
I appreciate your concern.

717
00:41:03.161 --> 00:41:05.801
but she's none of your business.

718
00:41:11.502 --> 00:41:15.312
You want to know why those
closest to you betray you?

719
00:41:15.439 --> 00:41:17.669
Why you're alone and hunted?

720
00:41:17.676 --> 00:41:20.476
It's because even when you
try to do something good.

721
00:41:20.479 --> 00:41:25.079
you cannot seem to understand
where your selfishness ends

722
00:41:25.083 --> 00:41:27.852
and other people's lives begin.

723
00:41:27.853 --> 00:41:32.663
Now. if you'll excuse me. I'm
going home to people who love me.

724
00:41:39.697 --> 00:41:41.397
Raymond.

725
00:41:41.499 --> 00:41:43.129
It's Levine.

726
00:41:44.435 --> 00:41:45.195
David.

727
00:41:45.203 --> 00:41:46.743
Is this some kind of test?

728
00:41:46.744 --> 00:41:50.468
See if I would violate
client confidentiality?

729
00:41:50.475 --> 00:41:51.605
What did you find?

730
00:41:51.610 --> 00:41:52.140
You know what I found.

731
00:41:52.143 --> 00:41:57.047
David. the name of the account
holder who paid Isabella Stone.

732
00:41:57.048 --> 00:41:57.978
Who is it?

733
00:41:57.983 --> 00:41:59.517
It's you. Raymond.

734
00:41:59.518 --> 00:42:03.318
The money came
from one of your accounts.

735
00:42:03.487 --> 00:42:04.347
That's not possible.

736
00:42:04.356 --> 00:42:07.416
You have been
catastrophically compromised.

737
00:42:07.425 --> 00:42:10.485
<i>Forget having
your testicles scratched.</i>

738
00:42:10.495 --> 00:42:12.325
<i>You've been castrated.</i>
